name: Isle of Wight Festival 2024
summary: The Isle of Wight Festival 2024 is underway, with details on timings, lineup, and tickets available on Time Out UK. Viewers can catch the festival on TV through Radio Times. Bus services to the festival are outlined by the Isle of Wight County Press, while BBC reports on a golf buggy fire at the event. A tragic incident at a festival campsite resulted in a woman's death, reported by Southern Daily Echo. The Guardian reviews the festival and features performances by the Streets, the Prodigy, and the Pretenders. Portsmouth News shares a personal account of the late Keith Flint's 2016 performance with The Prodigy. BBC.com highlights transportation changes on the island due to the festival, and Island Echo describes the sunny arrival of revelers on the first day. Daily Mail reports on the discovery of a woman's body at the festival campsite and a separate fire at the event.

The match saw Leeds Rhinos emerge victorious against Leigh, accompanied by a record-breaking crowd. Fans also gathered at Odsal Stadium for a ride-out in his memory, while a funeral director in Whitehaven shared their touching memories of him.
